<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tags/Buyer-Guide on Create A Van Life</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/tags/buyer-guide/</link><description>Recent content in Tags/Buyer-Guide on Create A Van Life</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><copyright>© 2026 Create A Van Life</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/tags/buyer-guide/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>How We Test and Label Claims</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/how-we-test-and-label-claims/</link><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/how-we-test-and-label-claims/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Create A Van Life uses a &lt;strong&gt;recovery-first&lt;/strong&gt; lens: we rank products by how reliably they help you recover from drift and return to a stable weekly routine, not by headline specs alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We keep a &lt;strong&gt;700Wh+ minimum floor&lt;/strong&gt; because lower-capacity units are more likely to force charge-chasing in bad weather or tight refill windows. The goal is repeatable stability, not one good day.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Time to Recover Explained for Van Life Power</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/time-to-recover-explained/</link><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/time-to-recover-explained/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If your power plan feels stressful, this is the metric that usually fixes it: &lt;strong&gt;time to recover&lt;/strong&gt;. Instead of asking &amp;ldquo;How big is the battery?&amp;rdquo; ask &amp;ldquo;How quickly can I refill enough to erase drift and get stable again?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust link:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/how-we-test-and-label-claims/" &gt;How we test + how we label claims&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Fast-Charging Power Station Glossary (Van Life, Recovery-First)</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/fast-charging-power-station-glossary/</link><pubDate>Mon, 23 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/fast-charging-power-station-glossary/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If you’re shopping, start with the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/fast-charging-power-station-buyer-checklist/" &gt;Buyer Checklist&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, then use the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/fast-charging-buyer-guides/" &gt;Buyer Guides hub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This glossary exists to reduce confusion and prevent panic upgrades. We define terms in the way they matter for &lt;strong&gt;generator-free, recovery-first&lt;/strong&gt; van life.&lt;/p&gt;
